.TH "pm_noirq_op" 9 "pm_noirq_op" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pm_noirq_op \- Return the PM operation appropriate for given PM event.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "pm_callback_t" pm_noirq_op
.BI "(const struct dev_pm_ops *ops "  ","
.BI "pm_message_t state "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ops" 12
PM operations to choose from.
.IP "state" 12
PM transition of the system being carried out.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The driver of \fIdev\fP will not receive interrupts while this function is being
executed.
